# Private functions
  -- Own stack -- the harness `mk` shape, wired to the real shared facade
  @fn acceptInput()  @ 55
      -- Note entry and command dispatch both self-suppress while a toolbar widget holds focus, mirroring
      -- the main grid (trackerRender: inputAllowed folds focusState.acceptCmds). item==nil means dormant.
  -- Editing surface -- bind the pattern-editing subset of the tracker keymap
  -- Materialise the stored body onto the bound checkout take
  @fn materialiseNotes(specs)  @ 96-105
      -- Specs are park-shaped (logical-only). Route through the authoring add -- the same
      -- tm:addEvent tv's edit.add reaches -- so materialised notes are editable exactly like
      -- typed ones: addEvent takes logical ppq, stamps ppqL/endppqL, files a uuid. rpb rides
      -- like an authored note (tv stamps currentRpb); flush commits. see design/fx-patterns.md § Editing surface
  @fn curveDisplay(body)  @ 113-118
      -- columnDisplay flags for the curve column, from the body's domain + display hint:
      -- normalized -> pb thousandths (bipolar unless 'unipolar'); cc -> 14-bit unless 'cc7'.
  @fn materialiseCurve(body)  @ 120-131
  -- Write-through commit -- persist checkout edits back to the shared store
  @fn readbackBody()  @ 138-174
      -- Read channel 1 back through tm and rebuild the whitelisted body: notes drop fx/chan and fix
      -- lane 1, a curve normalises the pb column's cents to bipolar. lengthPpq/root ride the open
      -- snapshot (no bound command edits them). The field pick IS the whitelist. see design/fx-patterns.md § checkout model
  @fn writeThrough()  @ 178-185
      -- Fires on every mini rebuild; `armed` gates out the open/close rebuilds (bindTake, the
      -- materialise flush, the unbind) whose take is not yet/no longer the edited body.
  @fn cancel(close)  @ 190-194
      -- Esc discards: write-through already made the param track the edits, so restore the open
      -- snapshot with one guarded write. Enter needs no counterpart -- the param is already current.
  -- Modal editing surface
  @fn drawToolbar()  @ 278-290
      -- Mini toolbar: a copy of the tracker RPB ticker plus Commit/Cancel.
      -- see docs/patternEditor.md § Write-through commit for the button/pendingAction handoff.

# Public API (pe:*)
  @api pe:open(body, commit)  @ 201-249
      @contract  mint a checkout take on scratch, materialise `body`, bind the mini tm; `commit(newBody)` is the write-back  @ 198
      @contract  snapshots the body and arms write-through once materialised (open/close rebuilds stay silent)  @ 199
      @contract  an empty body (no lengthPpq) defaults its loop to one bar of the checkout take  @ 200
  @api pe:close()  @ 253-260
      @contract  sweep the pool metadata (write-through, so leaks without this)  @ 251
      @contract  unbind the mini tm, delete the checkout item  @ 252
  @api pe:isOpen()  @ 262
  @api pe:currentTake()  @ 263
  @api pe:draw()  @ 293-334
      @contract  draw pass -- toolbar row, grid fills the region below; popup sizes to fit  @ 292
  @api pe:handleInput(close)  @ 338-358
      @contract  input pass -- mouse, dispatch against mini cmgr, note entry; unconsumed Esc cancels, Enter commits  @ 336
      @contract  returns the dispatch result kr = { consumed, commandHeld }  @ 337
  @api pe:launch(body, commit)  @ 366-392
      @contract  production entry -- mint the checkout on `body` and raise the editing modal; onClose sweeps it  @ 365

